during the past six years have consistently used a Unit-of-Purchase methodology for computing both the current demand
charge adjustment and the monthly demand deferrals. Eastern Shore, however, states it is willing to revise its tariff
provisions to be effective May 19, 1994, in accordance with the Commission's Order to further clarify that both its
current demand charge adjustments and monthly demand deferrals will be calculated using a Unit-of-Purchase methodology.

