<SUMMARY>
SUMMARY: 

The U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service announces availability for public review of a technical/agency draft recovery
plan for Puerto Rican endangered ferns. They occur in the limestone or karst region of northwestern Puerto Rico and
in the central mountains. Deforestation and fragmentation of habitat may have restricted these species to their
present locations. The Service solicits review and comments from the public on this draft plan.



</SUMMARY>
<SUPPLEM>
SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION: 

Background




Restoring an endangered or threatened animal or plant to the point where it is again a secure, self-sustaining member
of its ecosystem is a primary goal of the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service's endangered species program. To help guide
